The paper deals with algorithms for sampling and counting satisfying assignments to CNF formulas, which are problems in the area of computational complexity. The use of Markov chains and the Lov\'{a}sz local lemma suggest connections to the areas of randomized algorithms (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which could place it in the areas of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or machine learning (cs.LG).
